============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is the Renaissance?
A1: The Renaissance (14th-17th century) was a cultural
     rebirth in Europe featuring renewed interest in Greco-
     Roman art, humanism, and early science. Began in Italy;
     spread across Europe.

Q2: What is the Magna Carta?
A2: The Magna Carta (1215) was a charter limiting royal
     power in England, establishing that the king is subject
     to law. It influenced modern constitutional law and
     human rights.

Q3: What is artificial intelligence?
A3: AI is the simulation of human intelligence by machines,
     including learning, reasoning, and problem-solving.
     Types: narrow AI (specific tasks) and general AI
     (human-level across domains).

Q4: What is capitalism?
A4: Capitalism is an economic system where private
     individuals own the means of production and markets
     determine prices and production through supply and
     demand.

Q5: What is democracy?
A5: Democracy is government where power derives from the
     people through free elections, rule of law, and
     protection of minority rights. Types include direct and
     representative democracy.

